To run the front end, run `npm run dev` from root

To run the backend end for the first time,
replace the template connection string in secret.js

Also use the cmd `git update-index --assume-unchanged packages/express-backend/secret.js`
from the root directory to prevent your connection string from overiding the template

then run the cmd `npm run dev` from the express-backend directory

## Contributing

Please install the Prettier and ESLint extensions in your editor.
Use the standards described by .prettierrc and eslint.config.js in root, and default to https://google.github.io/styleguide/jsguide.html otherwise.

### Linting

Prettier: npm run lint, npm run lint-fix
ESLint: npm run format, npm run check-format